text: Tetragramma is a genus of fossil sea urchins known from the Upper Jurassic (Oxfordian) to the Upper Cretaceous (Turonian). ==Species== Species include:Kroh, A. (2010). Tetragramma L. Agassiz, 1838 †. In: Kroh, A. & Mooi, R. (2015) World Echinoidea Database.
